Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat with a knob of @butter{to taste} or @oil{to taste}.

When hot, fry the garlic for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @rice{150%grams} and @salted water{300%ml}. Bring to the boil then lower heat to medium and cover.

Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat and leave aside for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (keep covered so the rice can continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, drain the @tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Quarter the @mushrooms{250%g}, halving any larger pieces.

Place a separate pot over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the tofu and mushrooms for ~{7-10%minutes}. Shift frequently to ensure they don't burn. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Korma Curry Paste{1%sachet} to the tofu and mushrooms. Fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in the @Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic{1%pack}, @water{50%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Cover and simmer until the mushrooms are tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @?sugar{to taste} (if required).

Roughly chop the @chives{5%g}(roughly chopped) (use #scissors{} if you prefer).

Divide the tofu curry between #bowls{} and serve the garlic rice alongside.

Finish with a sprinkling of chopped chives.

> This aromatic veggie curry is a tapestry of tastes and textures. Crispy tofu, charred mushrooms, zippy chives and fragrant garlic rice are only a few of the elements that make this dish delicious.